Vice President Pence gave a speech at Yad Vashem in Jerusalem, Israel, to mark the 75th anniversary of the liberation of Auschwitz. He emphasized the importance of remembering the Holocaust and the millions of lives lost. Pence also paid tribute to the survivors and the Allied forces who freed Europe from tyranny. He called for unity in standing against anti-Semitism and specifically mentioned the threat of the Islamic Republic of Iran. Pence praised the resilience of the Jewish people and reaffirmed the strong bond between the United States and Israel. The speech concluded with a prayer for peace.